<section id="author-information" class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content-section">
            <h2>General Guidelines to Authors</h2>
            <p>IEEE RECCAP 2026 invites contributions from academic, government, and industry-based researchers. The following guidelines are provided to help authors prepare and submit their papers for the 2026 IEEE RECCAP. Discover the topics of the conference on the official website.</p>
            <p>Please read all instructions thoroughly before proceeding. Once reviewed, scroll to the bottom of the page to upload your manuscript.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Originality:</strong> Submitted manuscripts must be written as technical papers presenting original, unpublished research. The work must not be under review by any other conference or journal.</li>
                <li><strong>Format and Length:</strong> Contributions should be a regular paper (4-6 pages) formatted in double-column IEEE conference style. Authors should use the official IEEE conference templates available for both MS Word and LaTeX. Submissions that do not conform to the required style may be rejected without review. All manuscripts must be submitted electronically in PDF format and must be clearly readable. All papers must be submitted via Microsoft CMT. For detailed formatting guidelines, please refer to the <a href="https://www.ieee.org/conferences/publishing/templates" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Conference Template</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Plagiarism Policy:</strong> Each submission will undergo a mandatory plagiarism check in accordance with IEEE standards. Any paper found violating ethical or plagiarism policies will be immediately rejected, and the authors’ affiliated institutions will be notified.</li>
                <li><strong>Review Process:</strong> All papers will be evaluated through a single-blind peer-review process conducted by the Program Committee. Review criteria include correctness, originality, technical depth, contribution significance, clarity, and relevance to the conference themes.</li>
                <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Papers failing to meet the required formatting, page limit, or anonymization standards will be rejected without review.</li>
                <li><strong>Registration and Presentation:</strong> At least one author of every accepted paper must register for the conference and present the paper. Each accepted paper requires a separate author registration.</li>
                <li><strong>Copyright Agreement:</strong> In accordance with IEEE policy, the authors of all accepted papers must sign a copyright transfer agreement. Detailed instructions will be provided after paper acceptance.</li>
                <li><strong>Submission Portal:</strong> Manuscripts must be uploaded through the submission link provided at the bottom of this page.<br>
                <strong>Submission Link:</strong> <a href="https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/RECCAP2026" target="_blank">https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/RECCAP2026</a></li>
                <li><strong>Publication:</strong> Accepted and presented papers will be submitted to IEEE Xplore for possible publication, ensuring global visibility and recognition.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content-section">
            <div class="alert alert-info">
                <h4>Submission Portal</h4>
                <p>Upload your manuscript via Microsoft CMT online submission system.</p>
                <a href="https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/RECCAP2026" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Go to Submission Portal</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section" id="paper-presentation-guidelines">
            <h2>Paper Presentation Guidelines</h2>
            <p>Accepted paper presenters for RECCAP 2026 are requested to follow the presentation instructions below.</p>
            <div class="presentation-resource-card">
                <div class="presentation-resource-copy">
                    <span>Presentation Upload</span>
                    <h3>Upload your presentation PDF and use the official slide template</h3>
                    <p>Submit the final presentation PDF through the upload form. The official RECCAP 2026 PPT template is available below for preparing your slides.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="presentation-resource-actions">
                    <a href="{{paperPresentationUploadForm}}" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        <i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"></i> Upload Presentation
                    </a>
                    <a href="{{slideTemplatePptx}}" class="btn btn-outline-primary" download>
                        <i class="bi bi-download"></i> Download PPT Template
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="presentation-template-embed">
                <object data="{{slideTemplatePptx}}"
                    type="application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation">
                    <p>
                        Your browser may not preview PPTX files inline.
                        <a href="{{slideTemplatePptx}}" download>Download the RECCAP 2026 slide template</a>.
                    </p>
                </object>
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Presentation Duration:</strong> The total presentation duration is 15 minutes, including
                    12 minutes for the presentation and 3 minutes for Q&amp;A. Presenters are requested to strictly
                    adhere to the allotted time.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Slide Limit:</strong> The maximum number of slides allowed is 12 slides. Please keep the
                    content concise and readable.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Upload Format:</strong> All presentations must be uploaded in PDF format only. Convert
                    PPT/PPTX files to PDF before submitting.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>File Size:</strong> The maximum file size allowed for upload is 20 MB. Please compress the
                    PDF if required.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Updates:</strong> Authors can submit updates by simply submitting the form again. Only the
                    latest submission will be considered.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Deadline:</strong> The upload/update form will remain open until 18 May 2026. No
                    modifications will be accepted after the deadline.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>File Name:</strong> The presentation file name should be in the format
                    <strong>PIDXXX.pdf</strong>, where XXX is your Paper ID.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
